      "message": "Cool!\n\nI do recommend using Fetcher, since it implements pre-fetching, buffering, and direct logs access. It should be better than a custom thing, and it is pretty decently tested. If you like this idea, you can grab the implementation from this CL:\n\nhttps://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/c8b8b3c82395ea7c43c88eb1ee9dc6f0a2ea87a6/logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/view/textlogs.go#160\n\nRenderer is a little less interesting, but do keep in mind that using it would ensure consistency between this endpoint and \"logdog cat\" tool. Not sure if that\u0027s valuable.",
